HEADWORD: Gamomorphism
<hw>Gam`o*mor"phism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
marriage + <grk>morfh`</grk> form, shape.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld>
<def>That stage of growth or development in an organism, in which the
reproductive elements are generated and matured in preparation for
propagating the species.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gamopetalous</ent>⟦br⟧
